                     2.0 TRANSLITERATION

     Transliteration switch:

     The programs  now  allow  the  user  to  mark  text  for
transliteration. The use is as follows:

     {~=     Transliteration on
     ~}      Transliteration off

     You may   mark  a  word,  phrase,  sentence,  paragraph,
section of the document,  or the total  document.  All  words
within   the   transliteration   codes   will   be   directly
transliterated.

     The code  works  best  when  used  with  paragraphs,  if
inserted against the far left margin (start and stop codes).

     We added  this  feature to allow addresses on letters to
be directly transliterated.  This feature will  also  convert
text from the Tel-Lex mode back into Cyrillics.


                            - 2 -

                3.0 BLACK AND WHITE MONITORS

     When you start LTGOLD or LTPRO,  you may now define your
monitor type as "BLACK AND  WHITE"  (works  well  with  older
laptop  computers).  In  order  to  accomplish  this  add the
following switch when running LTGOLD or LTPRO:

     3.1 C:\LTGOLD\LTGOLD -BW
     or  C:\LTGOLD\LTGOLD -BW+

     You will  notice  that  the  screen  layout  is slightly
different. This allows the program to give you a much sharper
image than the color version.

                    4.0 RUSSIAN HELP TEXT

     When you start LTGOLD or LTPRO,  you may now define  the
language you want the help text in (either English or Russian
at this time).  The default language is English.  In order to
have  Russian Help text add the following switch when running
LTGOLD or LTPRO:

     4.1 C:\LTGOLD\LTGOLD -HR

                    5.0 AUTOMATIC RUSSIAN

     LTGOLD and LTPRO have a program feature which allows  it
to  generate  the correct case and features of Russian words.
This feature is instead of the Russian words being programmed
into the Russian dictionary. If you find that the endings are
not to your liking,  you may disable this feature  by  adding
the following switch when running LTGOLD or LTPRO:

     5.1 C:\LTGOLD\LTGOLD -AR

NOTE: Sorry, in this version this feature does not work.

                6.0 PEEKING AT THE DICTIONARY

     The developers of LTGOLD found that  it  was  easier  to
work  on  the  dictionary  if  they  could  follow  what  the
dictionary selected when generating a sentence.  This  allows
for  easy  identification  of  problems if they should arise.
Users find this handy when looking for explanations as to the
reason  for a specific translation of a word.  It can also be
used to let us know if you find an error and what it is.

     We find it is easiest to use from the CON input  but  it
will  accept  files.  When  checking files be sure to turn on
Edit Each Sentence or the lists of words will run by you. You
should  also turn off "Display Synonyms" as you will see them
in the displayed text.

     Certain words will not display for linguistical reasons.
If you type "for, to, it, etc, all you may see is a period or
some other character.  Don't be alarmed, this is correct. The
translation may not look exactly like the words listed in the
display.  This is caused by the program doing a  linguistical
change  to  the words for proper attributes.  The base of the
word will look the same but ending may change. This is caused
by the programming of the Russian word.

                           - 3 -

     This feature  can  also  help  when using the additional
dictionary program to assure that words that  are  programmed
work properly To enable this feature add the following switch
when running LTGOLD or LTPRO:


     6.1 C:\LTGOLD\LTGOLD -@


                   7.0 AUTOMATIC MEANINGS

     One of  the unique features of LTGOLD and LTPRO is their
ability to allow the user to define the order of selection of
words  for  business  or  computer  meanings.  If  the second
dictionary is computer,  certain words will be  selected  for
their  meaning  as  they  apply  to this application.  If the
second dictionary is business then the meaning will be of the
business  nature.  If  only the Basic dictionary is enabled a
generic meaning of the word will be used.  The user should be
aware that unless the text is 100%  business or 100% computer
this option may be a problem.

     An example could be the word "drive".  If this option is
selected and the computer dictionary is enabled as the second
dictionary,  every time the program encounters the word drive
it will be translated into a computer disk drive.  A sentence
like, "We have to drive over and pick up the disk drive" will
not work as it will translate into "We  have  to  disk  drive
over to pick up the disk drive". This is a simple example but
we feel it is important to point out. To enable this feature,
either  select  it  from  the  "Format Output" section of the
Options menu from within the program  or  add  the  following
switch when running LTGOLD or LTPRO:

     7.1 C:\LTGOLD\LTGOLD -AM


                       8.0 HANDY HINTS

     8.1 MISSPELLED WORDS

     Most translation  programs  are  only  as  good  as  the
spelling of the words it reads.  We recommend that you always
use a spell checker to assure the program the  best  possible
translation.  We  realize  that not everyone spells correctly
and that there are common spelling  mistakes  that  are  made
time   after  time.  We  have  programmed  several  of  these
misspellings into the program to allow even a  document  with
misspellings  to end up being translated.  We programmed only
words that are not in conflict with other words.  If you  are
using  the  LTWORD program, always be sure to spell check any
word you add to the dictionary (both Russian and English).

                           - 4 -
     8.2 PUNCTUATION

     Second only   to  spelling,  correct  punctuation is  an
important requirement of any document to be translated. There
are several very good diction programs available to guarantee
you have put the correct punctuation into your  document.  We
use  Right  Writer,  but  there  are  several others that are
equally  effective.  LTGOLD  and  LTPRO   are   designed   to
compensate  for most punctuation errors but some may not have
been  anticipated.  Remember,  the  better  the  document  is
written, the better it will translate.

     8.3 LISTS OR ITEMS

     Unlike a  word for word translation program,  LTGOLD and
LTPRO translate,  sentence by sentence,  and take punctuation
marks  into  their  decision making process.  The end of each
sentence is assumed to be at the  period  (.).  The  programs
understand  most abbreviations as such.  Not seeing a period,
the programs will  create  one  at  the  512th  word  in  the
sentence.  This  concept  allows  both  LTGOLD  and  LTPRO to
produce very  accurate  translations  most  of  the  time.  A
problem  could  arise if you are translating a list or column
of words. The programs will create a sentence out of the list
and  translate  it  as  such.  In  order to prevent this from
happening,  you should put a period at the end of each  word,
phrase,  or individual statement you want translated.  If you
wanted to translate Dr.  Maslow's hierarchy  of  needs,  they
should be listed as:

                        Self-Esteem.
                        Recognition.
                            Love.
                          Security.
                          Physical.


                           - 5 -

            9.0 LTPRO MACHINE TRANSLATION FROM
         MICROSOFT(TM) WORD(TM) FOR WINDOWS(TM) 2.0

Several users of the LTGOLD and LTPRO programs have requested
access to these programs from the same macro features
available with WORD 5.0 5.5 and Multi Edit. We have created
a series of MACROS and other files which will now allow you to
translate documents or marked text while in WORD for WINDOWS
(WINWORD). We will explain the 3 MACROS and the reasons for
all three of them.


9.1  TRANSLATE THE WHOLE DOCUMENT NO MATTER WHAT THE SIZE IS

Go to the "Tools" command on your upper ribbon (while in
WINWORD). Select "Macro...". Name the Macro LTDOC (or another
name you feel comfortable with). Choose EDIT. Open File
LTDOC.DOC or enter the following text.

Sub MAIN
FileSaveAs.Name="c:\ltgold\winword.txt",.Format=5,.LockAnnot=0,
.Password=""
Shell "c:\ltgold\ltpro.pif", 0
End Sub

Close the Edit Window. Select Yes.

NOTE: You may change Name= to the path you want to use. DO NOT
use a file name you normally use as the Macro deletes the old
version without prompting you. This Macro creates output file
WINWORD.OUT. The 3rd Macro in this document will allow you to
import this file with your translation.


9.2 TRANSLATE ONLY MARKED TEXT FROM WINWORD

WINWORD does not have a means to export only marked text.
Having said this, we were be able to find a way to save the
portion of text you have marked and translate it. The problem
with this routine is that it does not allow you to select the
type of charactes you are exporting to the file. It only
allows you to export ASCII 7bit characters (Cyrillic's are
actually graphics in the 8th bit). The bottom line with this
routine is that you can only translate marked text which is
all English and if you send Russian out it will look like a
bunch of garbage. We hope that Microsoft will correct this in
the future.
Please create a Macro named LTSELECT (File LTSELECT.DOC),
following the same procedures as defined above. The Macro
should consist of the following 6 lines:

Sub MAIN
Open "c:\ltgold\winword.txt" For Output As #1
Print #1, Selection$()
Close #1
Shell "c:\ltgold\ltpro.pif", 0
End Sub

Always be sure to have highlighted text before running this
Macro and WINWORD will only allow a maximum of 32,000 bytes
of text in the highlighted area (several pages).

                           - 6 -


9.3 INSERT THE TRANSLATED TEXT BACK INTO YOUR DOCUMENT

The third Macro brings the translated text back into your
document. The reason this Macro could not be combined into
either of the first 2 Macros is that WINWORD does not process
each command prior to moving on to the next command. This
deficiency does not give the prior Macros enough time to save
your text and then translate it before bring the translated
text back into the document. One other point is that WINWORD
will not allow you to automatically define the format of the
text you are importing. Select DOS Text and the translated
text will be inserted at the same location as you have placed
the cursor. Please note that if the imported text looks like
garbage, you must highlight it and change the font to a
Cyrillic font. This Macro should be created the same as in the
two other Macros (use file LTINSERT.DOC).

Sub MAIN
InsertFile.Name="c:\ltgold\winword.out",.Range="",.Link=0
End Sub

If you highlight the text prior to running this Macro, your
marked text will be replaced with the translation. If you want
to keep the English, do NOT highlight the text.

After editing a Macro you may get a prompt asking if you want
to update the GLOSSARY. Please select Yes.

The last item you may edit is the LTPRO.PIF file for LTPRO.
You may change LTGOLD directory and Optional Parameters.
Please see your LTGOLD/LTPRO manual for the switches for
LTPRO. You should also read your Windows manual for additional
information on PIF files.

We will continue to keep our users updated on changes to
WINWORD which might correct some of the current deficiencies.

For additional assistance please contact us at (503) 370-7420,
in Salem, Oregon.
